    • playerReceiveOptions

      public int playerReceiveOptions​(Board board, int posXFrom, int posYFrom, int posXTo, int posYTo)
      Executes the power and notifies the player if the move wins the game
      Parameters:
      board - variable that contains the state of the board
      posXFrom - x coordinate of the worker that is going to use the power
      posYFrom - y coordinate of the worker that is going to use the power
      posXTo - x coordinate of the tile targeted by the power
      posYTo - y coordinate of the tile targeted by the power
      Returns:
      2 if the power usage wins the game, 1 if the turn step was the last one of the routine, 0 if there are other steps afterwards

    • getOptionsPlayer

      public OptionSelection getOptionsPlayer​(int upDiff, int downMin, boolean canIntoOpp, java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> limitations)
      Builds the object that contains all the options for a turn step, given the parameters
      Parameters:
      upDiff - Max levels the worker can climb up (aka level difference from start to destination tile)
      downMin - Minimum height of the cell to be acceptable
      canIntoOpp - True if the worker is allowed to go in a tile occupied by a worker of other players
      limitations - List of tiles the worker can't move to
      Returns:
      OptionSelection instance with all the player's options for that turn step
